     28-apr-2016
Status:
    works since 28-apr-2016
Recommended resolution:
    256x128x768 (same hyperdiffusion as in sample)
Comments:
    Disk in spherical coordinates with planet in corotational frame, inertial and indirect terms,
    plus Newton cooling with an optical depth dependant cooling time. 
Reference:
    Lyra, W., Richert, A.J.W., Boley, A., Turner, N., Mac Low, M.-M., Okuzumi, S., & Flock, M. 2016, ApJ, 817, 102.
    On shocks driven by high-mass planets in radiatively inefficient disks. II. Three-dimensional global disk simulations.
